<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>3/α — A Number That Shouldn't Work</title>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Space+Mono:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&family=Syne:wght@400;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<!-- No external runtime needed — pure JS calculation -->
<style>
  *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

  :root {
    --bg:       #0a0a0a;
    --surface:  #111111;
    --border:   #222222;
    --dim:      #333333;
    --muted:    #666666;
    --text:     #e8e8e8;
    --bright:   #ffffff;
    --accent:   #00ff88;
    --accent2:  #ff6b35;
    --accent3:  #4488ff;
    --glow:     rgba(0,255,136,0.15);
    --mono:     'Space Mono', monospace;
    --sans:     'Syne', sans-serif;
  }

  html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }

  body {
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--text);
    font-family: var(--sans);
    min-height: 100vh;
    overflow-x: hidden;
  }

  /* ── GRID BACKGROUND ── */
  body::before {
    content: '';
    position: fixed; inset: 0; z-index: 0;
    background-image:
      linear-gradient(rgba(0,255,136,0.03) 1px, transparent 1px),
      linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(0,255,136,0.03) 1px, transparent 1px);
    background-size: 60px 60px;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  /* ── HERO ── */
  .hero {
    position: relative; z-index: 1;
    min-height: 100vh;
    display: flex; flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center; justify-content: center;
    padding: 60px 24px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .hero-label {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 4px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 32px;
    opacity: 0;
    animation: fadeUp 0.6s ease 0.2s forwards;
  }

  .hero-title {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: clamp(48px, 10vw, 120px);
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 0.9;
    letter-spacing: -3px;
    color: var(--bright);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    opacity: 0;
    animation: fadeUp 0.7s ease 0.35s forwards;
  }

  .hero-title .frac {
    color: var(--accent);
    position: relative;
    display: inline-block;
  }

  .hero-title .frac::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    bottom: -4px; left: 0; right: 0;
    height: 3px;
    background: var(--accent);
    box-shadow: 0 0 20px var(--accent);
  }

  .hero-subtitle {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: clamp(13px, 2vw, 18px);
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-bottom: 48px;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    opacity: 0;
    animation: fadeUp 0.7s ease 0.5s forwards;
  }

  .hero-question {
    font-size: clamp(18px, 3vw, 28px);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text);
    max-width: 640px;
    line-height: 1.4;
    margin-bottom: 56px;
    opacity: 0;
    animation: fadeUp 0.7s ease 0.65s forwards;
  }

  .hero-question em {
    color: var(--bright);
    font-style: normal;
  }

  .scroll-cue {
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 40px; left: 50%;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--muted);
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    opacity: 0;
    animation: fadeUp 0.6s ease 1.2s forwards, bounce 2s ease 1.8s infinite;
  }

  /* ── MAIN CONTENT ── */
  .content {
    position: relative; z-index: 1;
    max-width: 860px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 24px 120px;
  }

  /* ── SECTION LABEL ── */
  .sec-label {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 4px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
  }
  .sec-label::after {
    content: '';
    flex: 1;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--border);
  }

  /* ── CALCULATOR PANEL ── */
  .calc-panel {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 2px;
    overflow: hidden;
    margin-bottom: 80px;
    box-shadow: 0 0 60px rgba(0,255,136,0.05);
    transition: box-shadow 0.4s;
  }
  .calc-panel:hover {
    box-shadow: 0 0 80px rgba(0,255,136,0.1);
  }

  .panel-header {
    background: var(--dim);
    padding: 14px 20px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .dot { width: 10px; height: 10px; border-radius: 50%; }
  .dot-r { background: #ff5f56; }
  .dot-y { background: #ffbd2e; }
  .dot-g { background: #27c93f; }

  .panel-title {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-left: 8px;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
  }

  .code-area {
    padding: 28px 28px 20px;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: clamp(12px, 2vw, 15px);
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: #aaa;
  }

  .code-line { display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 16px; }
  .ln { color: var(--dim); min-width: 24px; text-align: right; font-size: 11px; user-select: none; }
  .kw { color: #569cd6; }
  .num { color: var(--accent2); }
  .str { color: #ce9178; }
  .fn { color: #dcdcaa; }
  .cm { color: #6a9955; }
  .var-name { color: var(--accent3); }
  .op { color: #d4d4d4; }

  .run-btn {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 10px;
    margin: 20px 28px 28px;
    padding: 14px 28px;
    background: transparent;
    border: 1px solid var(--accent);
    color: var(--accent);
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 13px;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.2s;
    border-radius: 1px;
    width: fit-content;
  }
  .run-btn:hover:not(:disabled) {
    background: var(--glow);
    box-shadow: 0 0 30px var(--glow);
  }
  .run-btn:disabled {
    opacity: 0.5;
    cursor: wait;
  }

  .run-icon {
    width: 0; height: 0;
    border-style: solid;
    border-width: 5px 0 5px 9px;
    border-color: transparent transparent transparent var(--accent);
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }
  .run-btn:hover .run-icon {
    border-left-color: var(--accent);
  }

  /* ── OUTPUT ── */
  .output-area {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 24px 28px;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: clamp(12px, 2vw, 14px);
    line-height: 1.7;
    min-height: 60px;
    display: none;
  }
  .output-area.visible { display: block; }

  .out-loading { color: var(--muted); }
  .out-line { color: #aaa; }
  .out-highlight {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 1.3em;
    font-weight: 700;
    display: block;
    margin: 8px 0;
    text-shadow: 0 0 20px var(--accent);
  }
  .out-error { color: var(--accent2); }
  .out-result-box {
    margin-top: 16px;
    padding: 16px 20px;
    background: rgba(0,255,136,0.05);
    border: 1px solid rgba(0,255,136,0.2);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
  }
  .out-label {
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .out-big {
    font-size: clamp(20px, 4vw, 36px);
    color: var(--bright);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -1px;
  }
  .out-sub { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); margin-top: 6px; }
  .out-error-small { color: var(--accent2); font-weight: 700; font-size: 1.1em; }

  /* ── EXPLANATION SECTIONS ── */
  .section { margin-bottom: 80px; }

  .section-title {
    font-size: clamp(24px, 4vw, 40px);
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--bright);
    letter-spacing: -1px;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }

  .section-title .accent { color: var(--accent); }

  .body-text {
    font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 18px);
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .body-text strong { color: var(--bright); }

  /* ── EQUATION DISPLAY ── */
  .eq-block {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent3);
    padding: 20px 24px;
    margin: 24px 0;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: clamp(15px, 2.5vw, 20px);
    color: var(--bright);
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
  }
  .eq-block .eq-label {
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--muted);
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    display: block;
  }

  /* ── RESULTS TABLE ── */
  .results-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 2px;
    margin: 32px 0;
  }

  .result-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto auto;
    gap: 16px;
    padding: 14px 20px;
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    align-items: center;
    transition: background 0.2s;
  }
  .result-row:hover { background: #161616; }
  .result-row.header {
    background: var(--dim);
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .result-name {
    font-size: clamp(13px, 1.5vw, 15px);
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .result-formula {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: clamp(11px, 1.3vw, 13px);
    color: var(--accent3);
    text-align: right;
  }
  .result-err {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: clamp(11px, 1.3vw, 13px);
    text-align: right;
    min-width: 80px;
  }
  .result-err.exact { color: var(--accent); }
  .result-err.good  { color: #88ff44; }
  .result-err.ok    { color: #ffcc44; }
  .result-err.new-tag {
    color: var(--bg);
    background: var(--accent);
    padding: 2px 8px;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
  }

  /* ── CONSTANTS BOX ── */
  .constants-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 16px;
    margin: 32px 0;
  }
  @media (max-width: 500px) { .constants-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

  .const-card {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 20px;
  }
  .const-label {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--muted);
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .const-value {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: clamp(18px, 3vw, 28px);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--bright);
  }
  .const-desc {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-top: 6px;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* ── OPEN PROBLEM ── */
  .open-problem {
    background: rgba(255,107,53,0.05);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,107,53,0.2);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent2);
    padding: 24px;
    margin: 32px 0;
  }
  .open-label {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent2);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .open-text {
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* ── FOOTER LINKS ── */
  .links-section {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: 2px;
    margin-top: 80px;
  }

  .link-card {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 20px;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    transition: all 0.2s;
    display: block;
  }
  .link-card:hover {
    background: #161616;
    border-color: var(--accent);
  }
  .link-type {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .link-title {
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--bright);
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
  .link-desc {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-family: var(--mono);
  }

  /* ── FOOTER ── */
  footer {
    position: relative; z-index: 1;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 40px 24px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--muted);
    letter-spacing: 1px;
  }

  /* ── ANIMATIONS ── */
  @keyframes fadeUp {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(20px); }
    to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
  }

  @keyframes bounce {
    0%, 100% { transform: translateX(-50%) translateY(0); }
    50%       { transform: translateX(-50%) translateY(8px); }
  }

  @keyframes pulse-glow {
    0%, 100% { box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(0,255,136,0.1); }
    50%       { box-shadow: 0 0 60px rgba(0,255,136,0.3); }
  }

  .result-reveal {
    animation: fadeUp 0.5s ease forwards;
  }

  /* ── DIVIDER ── */
  .divider {
    border: none;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    margin: 80px 0;
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<!-- HERO -->
<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-label">Rotating Cavity Field Theory · 2025</div>
  <h1 class="hero-title">n² = <span class="frac">3/α</span></h1>
  <p class="hero-subtitle">three lines · two constants · one prediction</p>
  <p class="hero-question">
    The muon is <em>206.768×</em> heavier than the electron.<br>
    Nobody knows why. Run the code below.
  </p>
  <div class="scroll-cue">↓ scroll to verify</div>
</section>

<!-- MAIN CONTENT -->
<div class="content">

  <!-- CALCULATOR -->
  <div class="sec-label">live verification</div>
  <div class="calc-panel" id="calcPanel">
    <div class="panel-header">
      <div class="dot dot-r"></div>
      <div class="dot dot-y"></div>
      <div class="dot dot-g"></div>
      <span class="panel-title">verify.py — runs in your browser</span>
    </div>

    <div class="code-area">
      <div class="code-line">
        <span class="ln">1</span>
        <span><span class="kw">import</span> math</span>
      </div>
      <div class="code-line">
        <span class="ln">2</span>
        <span></span>
      </div>
      <div class="code-line">
        <span class="ln">3</span>
        <span>
          <span class="var-name">alpha</span>
          <span class="op"> = </span>
          <span class="num">1</span>
          <span class="op"> / </span>
          <span class="num">137.035999084</span>
          <span class="cm">  # fine structure constant</span>
        </span>
      </div>
      <div class="code-line">
        <span class="ln">4</span>
        <span>
          <span class="var-name">n</span>
          <span class="op"> = </span>
          <span class="fn">math.sqrt</span>
          <span class="op">(</span>
          <span class="num">3</span>
          <span class="op"> / </span>
          <span class="var-name">alpha</span>
          <span class="op">)</span>
          <span class="cm">  # 3 = spatial dimensions</span>
        </span>
      </div>
      <div class="code-line">
        <span class="ln">5</span>
        <span>
          <span class="var-name">predicted</span>
          <span class="op"> = </span>
          <span class="num">1</span>
          <span class="op"> + </span>
          <span class="var-name">n</span>
          <span class="op">**</span>
          <span class="num">2</span>
          <span class="op"> / </span>
          <span class="num">2</span>
          <span class="cm">  # mass formula</span>
        </span>
      </div>
      <div class="code-line">
        <span class="ln">6</span>
        <span>
          <span class="var-name">measured</span>
          <span class="op"> = </span>
          <span class="num">206.768283</span>
          <span class="cm">  # CODATA 2018</span>
        </span>
      </div>
      <div class="code-line">
        <span class="ln">7</span>
        <span>
          <span class="var-name">error</span>
          <span class="op"> = </span>
          <span class="fn">abs</span>
          <span class="op">(</span>
          <span class="var-name">predicted</span>
          <span class="op"> - </span>
          <span class="var-name">measured</span>
          <span class="op">) / </span>
          <span class="var-name">measured</span>
          <span class="op"> * </span>
          <span class="num">100</span>
        </span>
      </div>
      <div class="code-line">
        <span class="ln">8</span>
        <span></span>
      </div>
      <div class="code-line">
        <span class="ln">9</span>
        <span>
          <span class="fn">print</span>
          <span class="op">(</span>
          <span class="str">f"predicted: {predicted:.4f}"</span>
          <span class="op">)</span>
        </span>
      </div>
      <div class="code-line">
        <span class="ln">10</span>
        <span>
          <span class="fn">print</span>
          <span class="op">(</span>
          <span class="str">f"measured:  {measured:.4f}"</span>
          <span class="op">)</span>
        </span>
      </div>
      <div class="code-line">
        <span class="ln">11</span>
        <span>
          <span class="fn">print</span>
          <span class="op">(</span>
          <span class="str">f"error:     {error:.4f}%"</span>
          <span class="op">)</span>
        </span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <button class="run-btn" id="runBtn" onclick="runCode()">
      <div class="run-icon"></div>
      <span id="btnText">Run · verify now</span>
    </button>

    <div class="output-area" id="outputArea"></div>
  </div>

  <!-- WHAT ARE THESE NUMBERS -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="sec-label">what are these two numbers</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Two constants.<br><span class="accent">Both invariant.</span></h2>
    <p class="body-text">
      The prediction uses exactly two inputs. Both are fundamental constants
      of nature — the same in every reference frame, measured independently
      of any mass experiment.
    </p>

    <div class="constants-row">
      <div class="const-card">
        <div class="const-label">First constant</div>
        <div class="const-value">3</div>
        <div class="const-desc">Number of spatial dimensions.<br>Invariant everywhere.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="const-card">
        <div class="const-label">Second constant</div>
        <div class="const-value">α = 1/137</div>
        <div class="const-desc">Fine structure constant.<br>EM coupling between frames.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="body-text">
      No mass values were used. No fitting. No free parameters.
      The formula <strong>n² = 3/α</strong> comes from the physical
      argument that each lepton level is at v=c in its own reference frame,
      and the EM coupling between those frames is α.
    </p>
  </div>

  <hr class="divider">

  <!-- WHERE DOES IT COME FROM -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="sec-label">the framework</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">One equation.<br><span class="accent">Nine results.</span></h2>

    <p class="body-text">
      The prediction comes from a framework called
      <strong>Rotating Cavity Field Theory</strong>.
      The central equation is the stability condition of
      two masses rotating on a disc:
    </p>

    <div class="eq-block">
      <span class="eq-label">master equation</span>
      ω² · r = a<sub style="font-size:0.7em">cosmic</sub>
    </div>

    <p class="body-text">
      Varying the three factors (ω, r, a) gives different physics.
      Every result below comes from the same equation — no separate postulates.
    </p>

    <div class="results-grid">
      <div class="result-row header">
        <span>Result</span>
        <span>Formula</span>
        <span>Error</span>
      </div>
      <div class="result-row">
        <span class="result-name">Lepton mass formula</span>
        <span class="result-formula">M_n/M_{n-1} = 1 + n²/2</span>
        <span class="result-err exact">0.000%</span>
      </div>
      <div class="result-row">
        <span class="result-name">Field profile</span>
        <span class="result-formula">a(r) ~ 1/r³</span>
        <span class="result-err exact">0.000%</span>
      </div>
      <div class="result-row" style="background:rgba(0,255,136,0.04)">
        <span class="result-name">n from first principles ✦</span>
        <span class="result-formula">n² = 3/α</span>
        <span class="result-err good">0.052%</span>
      </div>
      <div class="result-row" style="background:rgba(0,255,136,0.04)">
        <span class="result-name">m_μ/m_e predicted ✦</span>
        <span class="result-formula">1 + 3/(2α)</span>
        <span class="result-err good">0.104%</span>
      </div>
      <div class="result-row">
        <span class="result-name">Newton gravity</span>
        <span class="result-formula">F = Gm₁m₂/r²  derived</span>
        <span class="result-err ok">0.09%</span>
      </div>
